otcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6308x4206+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F65%2F24fc11eb484b8da9d35348261f7e%2Fgettyimages-2221489897.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6308x4206+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F65%2F24fc11eb484b8da9d35348261f7e%2Fgettyimages-2221489897.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6308x4206+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F65%2F24fc11eb484b8da9d35348261f7e%2Fgettyimages-2221489897.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6308x4206+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F65%2F24fc11eb484b8da9d35348261f7e%2Fgettyimages-2221489897.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6308x4206+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F65%2F24fc11eb484b8da9d35348261f7e%2Fgettyimages-2221489897.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6308x4206+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F65%2F24fc11eb484b8da9d35348261f7e%2Fgettyimages-2221489897.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6308x4206+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F65%2F24fc11eb484b8da9d35348261f7e%2Fgettyimages-2221489897.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6308x4206+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F65%2F24fc11eb484b8da9d35348261f7e%2Fgettyimages-2221489897.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6308x4206+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F65%2F24fc11eb484b8da9d35348261f7e%2Fgettyimages-2221489897.jpg" class="img" alt="Kenya&amp;#039;s Faith Kipyegon reacts at the end of her race after taking part in the &amp;quot;Breaking4&amp;quot; event, in an attempt to become the first woman to run a mile in under four minutes, at Stade Charlety on June 26, 2025 in Paris." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Kenya's Faith Kipyegon reacts at the end of her race after taking part in the "Breaking4" event, in an attempt to become the first woman to run a mile in under four minutes, at Stade Charlety on June 26, 2025 in Paris.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Emma Da Silva/AFP via Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;Kenya's Faith Kipyegon attempted to become the first woman to run a mile in under 4 minutes yesterday, but her &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/06/26/nx-s1-5445959/4-minute-mile-kipyegon" target="_blank"&gt;personal best came up short&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Anna Wintour announced yesterday that she would be &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/06/26/nx-s1-5447474/anna-wintour-vogue-conde-nast" target="_blank"&gt;stepping down as head of editorial content&lt;/a&gt; at American &lt;em&gt;Vogue&lt;/em&gt; after nearly 40 years in the role.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Dune&lt;/em&gt; director Denis Villeneuve has signed on to &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/06/26/nx-s1-5446011/james-bond-denis-villeneuve-dune-director" target="_blank"&gt;lead the next installment&lt;/a&gt; of the James Bond franchise.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
