o-2-eric-johnson-right-with-his-husband-dennis-hopkinsleft-4-years-in.JPG 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/480x270+0+17/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd2%2F84%2F45ccb579414094fa29939ed28f75%2Fphoto-2-eric-johnson-right-with-his-husband-dennis-hopkinsleft-4-years-in.JPG 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/480x270+0+17/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd2%2F84%2F45ccb579414094fa29939ed28f75%2Fphoto-2-eric-johnson-right-with-his-husband-dennis-hopkinsleft-4-years-in.JPG 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/480x270+0+17/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd2%2F84%2F45ccb579414094fa29939ed28f75%2Fphoto-2-eric-johnson-right-with-his-husband-dennis-hopkinsleft-4-years-in.JPG 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/480x270+0+17/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd2%2F84%2F45ccb579414094fa29939ed28f75%2Fphoto-2-eric-johnson-right-with-his-husband-dennis-hopkinsleft-4-years-in.JPG 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/480x270+0+17/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd2%2F84%2F45ccb579414094fa29939ed28f75%2Fphoto-2-eric-johnson-right-with-his-husband-dennis-hopkinsleft-4-years-in.JPG 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/480x270+0+17/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd2%2F84%2F45ccb579414094fa29939ed28f75%2Fphoto-2-eric-johnson-right-with-his-husband-dennis-hopkinsleft-4-years-in.JPG" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/480x270+0+17/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd2%2F84%2F45ccb579414094fa29939ed28f75%2Fphoto-2-eric-johnson-right-with-his-husband-dennis-hopkinsleft-4-years-in.JPG" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/480x270+0+17/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd2%2F84%2F45ccb579414094fa29939ed28f75%2Fphoto-2-eric-johnson-right-with-his-husband-dennis-hopkinsleft-4-years-in.JPG" class="img" alt="Eric Johnson (right) with his husband, Dennis Hopkins (left)." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Eric Johnson (right) with his husband, Dennis Hopkins (left).                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Courtesy of Eric Johnson                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;Eric Johnson's husband, Dennis Hopkins, was given a 50% chance of surviving his next round of treatments for stage four lung cancer. During a hospital stay, the couple met their unsung hero: a nurse named Sherry, who &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/06/23/nx-s1-5438553/a-kind-no-nonsense-nurse-helped-a-couple-prepare-for-death" target="_blank"&gt;offered straightforward insights&lt;/a&gt; that helped them navigate the following days with a sense of peace.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A federal judge in San Francisco on Monday &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/06/25/nx-s1-5445242/federal-rules-in-ai-companys-favor-in-landmark-copyright-infringement-lawsuit-authors-bartz-graeber-wallace-johnson-anthropic" target="_blank"&gt;ruled in favor of AI company Claude&lt;/a&gt; in a copyright infringement case against a group of authors. The first-of-its-kind ruling could allow AI companies to train their language models on copyrighted works.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Morgan Wallen's album &lt;em&gt;I'm the Problem &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/06/25/g-s1-74543/morgan-wallen-brandon-lake-charts" target="_blank"&gt;remains at the top&lt;/a&gt; of the&lt;em&gt; Billboard &lt;/em&gt;200 albums chart for the fifth consecutive week as it vies for "album of the summer."&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
